			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong><span class="subheadline">Role</span></strong></p>
<p>
	To join our expanding R&amp;D team developing the worlds&#39; most advanced image analysis products and technologies we are seeking for our headquarters in Munich a high <span>calibre</span> Quality Assurance Engineer.</p>
<div class="normal">
	<p align="justify">
		In this exciting role you will work within a team of QA engineers and will be responsible for the development and execution of test cases for specific areas of of our products functionality. These tests include user interface, workflow, new algorithms and client server processing. You will have a QA or Software Engineering background with a minimum of 2 years experience working with sophisticated client server software. You will have an existing knowledge of Quality Assurance processes and methods.<br />
		<br />
		<strong><span class="subheadline">Responsibilities</span></strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Develop and execute test cases to ensure the quality of Definiens&#39; products meets our customers&#39; high expectations</li>
		<li>
			Develop and execute manual and automated testing procedures for areas including algorithmic, workflow&nbsp;and GRID processing areas of platform functionality&nbsp;</li>
		<li>
			Keep effective records of QA plans and work within our ISO-9001 quality management system&nbsp;</li>
		<li>
			Work reliably and to time, providing accurate status reports to QA and Engineering Management</li>
		<li>
			Acquire and maintain detailed knowledge of aspects of the platform functionality</li>
		<li>
			Reproduce and qualify technical issues reported with new developments and existing products&nbsp;</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		<strong><span class="subheadline">Qualifications &amp; Skills</span></strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Degree in Computer Science, Biomedical Engineering, Mathematics or Physics</li>
		<li>
			Minimum 2 years work experience in Quality Assurance or Development capacity dealing with sophisticated and technically focused client server products</li>
		<li>
			Working knowledge of Windows client and server and Linux Operating Systems&nbsp;</li>
		<li>
			Working knowledge of a modern programming or scripting language</li>
		<li>
			Troubleshooting and deductive reasoning skills</li>
		<li>
			High level of self motivation and a good attention to detail</li>
		<li>
			Ability to work in a fast-paced, small company environment with iterative development methodology</li>
		<li>
			Strong verbal and written communication skills in English and German</li>
		<li>
			An interest in image based or image analysis applications (any previous experience would be a bonus)&nbsp;</li>
		<li>
			ISTQB foundation level certification would be a plus</li>
		<li>
			Must be a team player<br />
			&nbsp;</li>
	</ul>
	<strong><span class="subheadline">We offer</span></strong><br />
	<br />
	<ul>
		<li>
			A challenging and rewarding position at the cutting edge of image analysis</li>
		<li>
			The opportunity to work within a highly motivated and qualified team of experts</li>
		<li>
			A stimulating cosmopolitan working environment in Munich</li>
		<li>
			Excellent working conditions with comprehensive benefits and ongoing career and professional development</li>
	</ul>
